---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="About">
  <section class="hero">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>About me</h1>
  </section>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      I'm Youssef Sawiris. I'm a software engineer and a 6th grade math teacher.
      The combination is unusual but it's how I want to spend this stretch of my life.
    </p>

    <h2>Engineering</h2>
    <p>
      I spent several years as a software engineer, most recently at
      <strong>Strava</strong>. I work mostly in TypeScript, Python, and React, and lately I've
      been building <a href="/engineering/">LLM-powered agents</a> for narrow domains —
      municipal permit applications, news, scheduling, education. In undergrad I also ran
      <a href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLZ_SI6zSFXvCFiWtGFy4U3X3f1dAj9zGz">YoYo Code Club</a>
      on YouTube, a small beginner Python + JavaScript video series.
    </p>

    <h2>Teaching</h2>
    <p>
      In January 2025 I started teaching 6th grade math at
      <strong>Lodestar</strong>, a public charter school in East Oakland. I'm completing my
      teaching credential through the
      <a href="https://www.reachinst.org/">Reach Institute for School Leadership</a>.
      Most of my classroom work — <a href="/teaching/">culture, lesson design, reflection</a> — sits in the teaching section.
    </p>

    <h2>Why both</h2>
    <p>
      Engineering taught me how to build systems. Teaching is teaching me how those systems
      meet kids in a room. Both jobs are about figuring out what someone actually needs and
      then doing the work — patiently, in public — to give it to them. The tools I build now
      sit at that intersection.
    </p>

    <h2>Background</h2>
    <p>
      I'm Coptic Egyptian, born and raised in California. Outside of work I'm usually on a bike,
      with family, or at my parish.
    </p>

